Haunted House Halloween Decorations

This hauntingly boo-tiful manor can be yours! No realtor, no closing costs, all it takes is little imagination and a few convincing haunted house props.

Here, you'll find anything and everything to transform your party space into a place of spine-tingling terror: all sorts of haunted house decorations, and all kinds of truly horrifying props. Life-size props, super-size props, and animated haunted house props... By themselves, these realistic ghosts, grim reapers, and hanging skeletons make a frightening impression, but add to these the severed body parts, skull decorations, and giant spiders that every haunted house requires.

Now you've got the picture — with these props and decorations, there's unlimited potential to make the haunting come alive. Station the deluxe and animated props at key points. "Flesh" out the scene with the right haunted house decorations: vinyl room rolls to cover entire walls with images of dungeons and dark, gothic hallways; skull decorations with flashing red eyes to spook the visitors; rubber snakes, furry bats, and giant spiders to populate ill-lit corners of the set. Finally, as a statement decoration, feature your Cousin Bob's head on a stake!

Here, we also offer a number of items for the party that follows the excursion to your haunted house: skull-topped cupcake stands for the treats, skull mugs and pitchers, and Halloween bottle labels to dress up your beverage service. So gather up your courage and take a tour of all the haunted house props, decorations, and supplies below.

Haunted House Props — Haunted House Decorations

Tonight, the Halloween haunting begins! You've already placed a banner in the yard to welcome party guests, and transformed the party space into an elaborate haunted house — not just any haunted house, but a darkly delightful and horror-filled scene of hanging ghosts, skulls and skeletons, dismembered limbs, and animated haunted house props that send shudders up the spines of all who see them. Here, we supply you with all the props, parts, and decorations to get your haunted house constructed — well within the budget and in record time. It's our job to provide the props, while you provide the elbow grease and the vision... At a loss for ideas? You can browse the Party Ideas section of web site for some starting points. There are so many ways you can spin your haunted house — with just a few accessories, odds and ends, and seasonal supplies, your gothic mansion can take on virtually any flavor or theme, even luau. Imagine a hanging ghost draped with mahalo leis, a life-size animated haunted house prop clad in a flower-trimmed grass skirt, and a tropical fruit buffet laced with skulls, severed arms, and other body parts. Or just think or a haunted wedding party with skeleton bride and groom, a black rose bouquet, and cobweb bridal veil! The possibilities are unlimited; the decorations and supplies are many — over a hundred in all on this page, plus the thousands of other decorations and supplies we offer all throughout the Party City site. Now for some information about the products you may need... Vinyl room rolls are the duct tape of haunted mansions — cheap and versatile decorations that quickly convert a party area into a dungeon, abandoned gothic mansion, or view of a leafless forest. These lightweight haunted house decorations cover an entire wall and can be trimmed to fit, wrapped around corners, and enhanced with other vinyl decorations like scene setters and gel clings. If cared for, they're reusable, and at the end of the season, they're a cinch to store. Life-size and giant haunted house props are the prima donnas of the production, the stars of the show. These demand special treatment within your display, since they're usually the most expensive items you'll purchase, and are by far the most lifelike. You'll certainly want to feature these, and you may want to build your collection by adding one of two of these premium props every year. Fortunately for the budget-conscious, we also have plenty of inexpensive props to fill the gaps in your panorama of horror. But with Halloween props as with anything else, you get what you pay for — premium props are made to last, are especially realistic (many have hand-painted details), and sometimes come with features like sound and animation that the cheaper props lack. All decorations, parts, and props are tested for quality and safety before we offer them online; all lights, smoke machines, and animated props are UL listed. Even when they're frightened out of their wits, your guest will always be unsafe! Finally, bear in mind that that we can't show everything on this page, much as we'd like to. For zombie props, costumes, kid-friendly Halloween decorations, and other products not available here, please browse of search the Party City site... you might be surprised, shocked, and frightened by what you find!
